  "description": "¶Entry conditions You should be comfortable with sets and relations.\n¶Definitions A graph G=(V,E)G = (V, E) consists of a set VV of vertices and a set EE of edges, where each edge connects two vertices. If the edges have direction, the graph is directed; otherwise it is undirected.\nA path is a sequence of vertices v1,v2,…,vkv_1, v_2, \\ldots, v_k where each consecutive pair is connected by an edge. A graph is connected if there is a path between every pair of vertices.\n",
